<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,684,1489,1669]" lastBlockId="7.[714,1247,170,289]" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName box="[177,436,1489,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Beilschmiedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moratii">
<emphasis box="[177,436,1489,1516]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">Beilschmiedia moratii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,263,1520,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Beilschmiedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="opposita">
<emphasis box="[151,263,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">B. opposita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[317,386,1520,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Beilschmiedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sary">
<emphasis box="[317,386,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">B. sary</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; these species are characterized by their subopposite leaves, black young twigs, dehiscent tepals in old flowers and their (nearly) glabrous condition. 
<taxonomicName box="[458,683,1612,1639]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Beilschmiedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moratii">
<emphasis box="[458,683,1612,1639]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">Beilschmiedia moratii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from both species in its obtuse to rounded leaf bases and the sparse, erect hairs on the inflorescences; from 
<taxonomicName box="[898,1020,201,226]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Beilschmiedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="opposita">
<emphasis box="[898,1020,201,226]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">B. opposita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it also differs in its raised reticulation and from 
<taxonomicName box="[1027,1098,232,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Beilschmiedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sary">
<emphasis box="[1027,1098,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="84">B. sary</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its smaller leaves.
</paragraph>
